## Getting Started

For local development and testing, you can run <strong>Bee nest</strong> in a container on your machine.

### Prerequisites

This is an example of how to list things you need to use the software and how to install them.
* npm
  ```sh
  npm install npm@latest -g
  ```
  
#### Container runtimes

You need to install a container runtime into each node in the cluster. 

This page lists details for using several common container runtimes, on Linux:

* [containerd](https://github.com/gabrielfeket/cubentainer/wiki/Getting-Started#containerd)
* [CRI-O](https://github.com/gabrielfeket/cubentainer/wiki/Getting-Started#cri-o)
* [Docker Engine](https://github.com/gabrielfeket/cubentainer/wiki/Getting-Started#docker-engine)


### Installation

1. Get a free API Key at [https://example.com](https://example.com)
2. Clone the repo
   ```sh

   ```
3. Install NPM packages
